data.chText: 负责人；（尤指）司令官，指挥官
data.enText: a person who is in charge of sth, especially an officer in charge of a particular group of soldiers or a military operation

data.chText: 军事 / 盟军 / 战地 / 飞行指挥官

data.enText: an officer of fairly high rank in the British or American navy
(in Britain) a London police officer of high rank

tr: someone in an official position of authority who can command or control others
a commissioned naval officer who ranks above a lieutenant commander and below a captain
an officer in command of a military unit

value.def: A commander is an officer in charge of a military operation or organization.

example.ex: The commander and some of the men had been released.
example.tran: 指挥官和一些士兵已经获释。

value.def: A commander is an officer in the Royal Navy or the U.S. Navy.
